    "body": "## Purpose\r\n\r\nThis PR persists FlashInfer autotune results to per-vLLM-config JSON files so later startups can reuse previously tuned FlashInfer GEMM/MoE tactics instead of profiling the same shapes again during warmup.\r\n\r\nBy default, cache files are stored under `$VLLM_CACHE_ROOT/flashinfer_autotune_cache/<flashinfer-version>/<arch>/<cache-hash>/autotune_configs.json`. Users can override the cache directory with `VLLM_FLASHINFER_AUTOTUNE_CACHE_DIR`.\r\n\r\nThe cache behavior follows FlashInfer's config caching API: <https://docs.flashinfer.ai/autotuning.html#config-caching>\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nvllm serve nvidia/Qwen3-30B-A3B-NVFP4 --enable-flashinfer-autotune\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Test Result\r\n\r\nThe server initialized successfully, ran FlashInfer autotuning for FP4 GEMM and TRTLLM FP4 MoE kernels, and saved a cache file under:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n/root/.cache/vllm/flashinfer_autotune_cache/0.6.11.post2/103a/c0e08888381a68086d35ad68ac110e90f879325c8377dda2c95c298d78a1f399/\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe directory contained one shared `autotune_configs.json` file, and inspecting the JSON file showed FlashInfer metadata and tuned configs.",
    "created_at": "2026-05-13T15:32:27Z",
